                  <summary>Sale of a female donkey by Horos to Epimachos from Philadelphia</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; the back is blank</note>
                     <note type="general">28 lines of writing by 2 ligatured and practiced hands</note>
                     <note type="general">The price seems relatively high</note>
                     <note type="general">The buyer may be identical with the Epimachos mentioned in P.Oxy. XLI 2981 and may have been a dealer in animals</note>
                     <note type="general">It is notable that the buyer is from the Fayum and that probably he was not buying for his own use, but to resell; A. Joerdens, Tyche 10 (1995) 37-100, argues that this was not usually the case</note>
